VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT >\s*(?:/etc/|/root/|~/)(?:passwd|shadow|sudoers|ssh|\.ssh|crontab)\b
WHEN EXPR MISSING:# intentional|test|example
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects writes to sensitive system files including shadow, sudoers, and SSH configuration.
TRACE Externalized rule logic for World-Readable Sensitive File Write.
